{% extends 'includes/layout.njk' %}

{% from 'components/tables/macro.njk' import table %}
{% from 'components/panel/macro.njk' import panel %}

{% block breadcrumb %}
{{ breadcrumb({
  items: [
    {
      href: "/service-manual/",
      text: "Home"
    }
  ],
  href: "/service-manual/styles-components-patterns",
  text: "Styles, components and patterns"
}) }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">Table</h1>
      <p class="nhsuk-body-l nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-8">Use the table component to make information easier to compare and scan for users.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h2 >Code and design</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-full">
    <div class="app-example nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-4">
      {{ table({
      panel: true,
      heading: "Skin symptoms and possible causes",
      caption: "Skin symptoms and possible causes",
      firstCellIsHeader: false,
      head: [
          {
          text: "Skin symptoms"
          },
          {
          text: "Possible cause"
          }
      ],
      rows: [
          [
          {
              text: "Blisters on lips or around the mouth"
          },
          {
              text: "cold sores"
          }
          ],
          [
          {
              text: "Itchy, dry, cracked, sore"
          },
          {
              text: "eczema"
          }
          ],
          [
          {
              text: "Itchy blisters"
          },
          {
              text: "shingles, chickenpox"
          }
          ]
      ]
      }) }}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <p><a href="https://nhsuk.github.io/nhsuk-frontend/components/tables-panel.html">Preview the table in a panel component</a></p>
    <p>You can <a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-frontend/tree/master/packages/components/tables">get the latest table in a panel code</a> in the NHS.UK frontend library in GitHub.</p>
    <h2 id="when-to-use-this-component">When to use this a table</h2>
    <p>Use the table component to let users to compare information in rows and columns.</p>
    <h2 id="when-not-to-use-this-component">When not to use a table component</h2>
    <p>Never use the table component to layout content on a page. Instead, use the <a href="/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/grid">grid system</a>.</p>
    <h2 id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>
    <h3>Accessibility</h3>
    <p>Following webaim.org's <a href="https://webaim.org/techniques/tables/data">guidance for tables</a> we suggest:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Tables should have captions</li>
      <li>Use the scope attribute to associate the data cells with the appropriate headers</li>
      <li>Let the browser window determine the width of the table whenever possible, to reduce the horizontal scrolling required of those with low vision</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 id="table-captions">Table captions</h3>
    <p class="rich-text">Use the <code>&lt;caption&gt;</code> element to describe a table in the same way you would use a heading. A caption helps users find, navigate and understand tables.</p>
    <h3 id="table-headers">Table headers</h3>
    <p>Use table headers to tell users what the rows and columns represent.</p>
    <h2 id="reseach">Research</h2>
    <p>The table component tested well with users on conditions pages where the white panel helped scanability - when surrounded by text content.</p>
    <p>For context, its also worth noting that on the NHS website:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>tables never exceeded three columns, we didn't design for or test any tables over three columns.</li>
      <li>The majority of NHS website tables are text, a few contain data (numerical).</li>
      <li>We haven't uncovered any needs around re-ordering data in tables.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If youâ€™ve used this component, get in touch to share your user research findings.</p>
    <h2>Discuss</h2>
    <p>Discuss action links on the <a href="https://join.slack.com/t/nhs-service-manual/shared_invite/enQtNTIyOTEyNjU3NDkyLWUwOWM5MWY5MGRhYTYxZmY4ZWI0NDA1N2NhNTRiMGY3MTQxNjk5YTc3ZTAzMTA4YmE3ZDAxYmQ3MTQxNDgzOTQ">NHS.UK service manual Slack workspace</a> or email the standards team at <a href="mailto:service-manual@nhs.net">service-manual@nhs.net</a>.</p>
    <div class="nhsuk-review-date">
    <p class="nhsuk-body-s">Updated: January 2019</p>
    </div>
    {{ panel({
    "label": "Similar patterns",
    "HTML": "<ul>
                <li></li>
            </ul>"
    }) }}
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
